{"metadata":{"visual":{"presentation":{"themes":{"fc21f1ed-5881-480d-9b95-8e872c62a101":{"template":"basic","templateAdditionalOptions":{},"palette":{"primary":{"0":"#000000","5":"#131100","10":"#1f1c00","15":"#2a2600","20":"#353100","25":"#413c00","30":"#4e4800","35":"#5a5400","40":"#676000","50":"#827900","60":"#9d931d","70":"#b8ae38","80":"#d5c951","90":"#f2e66a","95":"#fff487","98":"#fffae4","99":"#fffbff","100":"#ffffff"},"secondary":{"0":"#000000","5":"#131100","10":"#1e1c05","15":"#29260e","20":"#ffa108","25":"#3f3c21","30":"#4b482c","35":"#575336","40":"#635f41","50":"#7c7858","60":"#969270","70":"#b1ac89","80":"#cdc7a3","90":"#eae3be","95":"#f8f2cb","98":"#fffae4","99":"#fffbff","100":"#ffffff"},"tertiary":"","error":{"0":"#000000","5":"#2d0001","10":"#410002","15":"#540003","20":"#690005","25":"#7e0007","30":"#93000a","35":"#a80710","40":"#ba1a1a","50":"#de3730","60":"#ff5449","70":"#ff897d","80":"#ffb4ab","90":"#ffdad6","95":"#ffedea","98":"#fff8f7","99":"#fffbff","100":"#ffffff"},"neutral":{"0":"#000000","5":"#12110c","10":"#1d1c16","15":"#272620","20":"#32302b","25":"#3d3b35","30":"#484740","35":"#54524c","40":"#605e57","50":"#797770","60":"#939089","70":"#aeaba3","80":"#cac6be","90":"#e6e2d9","95":"#f5f0e7","98":"#fef9f0","99":"#fffbff","100":"#ffffff"},"neutralVariant":{"0":"#000000","5":"#121107","10":"#1d1c11","15":"#28261a","20":"#323124","25":"#3e3c2f","30":"#49473a","35":"#555345","40":"#615f50","50":"#7a7768","60":"#949181","70":"#afab9b","80":"#cbc7b5","90":"#e7e3d0","95":"#f6f1de","98":"#fff9e7","99":"#fffbff","100":"#ffffff"}},"themeColors":{"primaryColor":"","secondaryColor":"","backgroundColor":"","primaryTextColor":"","textColor":""},"splashScreen":{"storedData":{"handle":"drive:/18PyQriZeRFxkIKog7JCiKnL1j5rsueXx","mimeType":"image/png","contentLength":1992196}}}},"theme":"fc21f1ed-5881-480d-9b95-8e872c62a101"}},"intent":"Mission: Functional Design for LUXE E-Commerce App\n\nTask: Define the Product Logic and User Workflows\n\nCore Features (The Browse Loop):\n\nCatalog: How does the user filter by category? Plan the search functionality and the \"Related Products\" section.\n\nProduct Details: Define all required data fields (Price, Images, Sizes/Colors, Stock status, Reviews).\n\nTransactional Logic (The Buy Loop):\n\nCart: How does the app handle quantity changes? Plan the local-to-cloud sync so the cart is saved across devices.\n\nCheckout: Map out the steps: Shipping Address -> Payment Selection -> Final Review -> Order Confirmation.\n\nPayments: Detail the process for M-Pesa STK Push and Stripe card payments.\n\nUser Management:\n\nProfile: Plan the \"Order History\" view and the \"Saved Addresses\" management.\n\nAuth: Define the signup flow and how a user's session is maintained.\n\nDatabase Logic:\n\nPlan the table structures for products, cart_items, and orders.\n\nSecurity: Explicitly state the RLS (Row Level Security) rules so users only see their own private data.\n\nConstraint: Use Modern Retail design (No gradients/Glassmorphism). Ensure the plan supports real-time stock updates and offline viewing of previously loaded products.","revision_intents":[],"raw_intent":"Mission: Functional Design for LUXE E-Commerce App\n\nTask: Define the Product Logic and User Workflows\n\nCore Features (The Browse Loop):\n\nCatalog: How does the user filter by category? Plan the search functionality and the \"Related Products\" section.\n\nProduct Details: Define all required data fields (Price, Images, Sizes/Colors, Stock status, Reviews).\n\nTransactional Logic (The Buy Loop):\n\nCart: How does the app handle quantity changes? Plan the local-to-cloud sync so the cart is saved across devices.\n\nCheckout: Map out the steps: Shipping Address -> Payment Selection -> Final Review -> Order Confirmation.\n\nPayments: Detail the process for M-Pesa STK Push and Stripe card payments.\n\nUser Management:\n\nProfile: Plan the \"Order History\" view and the \"Saved Addresses\" management.\n\nAuth: Define the signup flow and how a user's session is maintained.\n\nDatabase Logic:\n\nPlan the table structures for products, cart_items, and orders.\n\nSecurity: Explicitly state the RLS (Row Level Security) rules so users only see their own private data.\n\nConstraint: Use Modern Retail design (No gradients/Glassmorphism). Ensure the plan supports real-time stock updates and offline viewing of previously loaded products.","parameters":{}},"assets":{},"title":"LUXE E-Commerce App","description":"Design a modern e-commerce app with robust features.","version":"0.0.1","nodes":[{"id":"node_step_luxe_design_content","metadata":{"title":"Generate LUXE Design Content","visual":{"x":700,"y":350,"collapsed":"expanded","outputHeight":88},"step_intent":"Generate a comprehensive functional design document for the LUXE e-commerce app. This document must cover core features (browse loop, catalog, product details), transactional logic (buy loop, cart, checkout, payments), user management (profile, authentication), database logic (table structures for products, cart_items, orders), and security (RLS rules). Ensure the design adheres to Modern Retail principles (no gradients/glassmorphism) and supports real-time stock updates and offline viewing of previously loaded products. The text_generation_agent will use the entire application description as its prompt to produce this detailed plan."},"type":"embed://a2/generate.bgl.json#module:main","configuration":{"config$prompt":{"parts":[{"text":"## Objective\nThe objective is to generate a comprehensive, high-fidelity functional design document for the \"LUXE\" e-commerce application. The document must serve as a technical and design blueprint, ensuring all core features, transactional logic, user management, database structures, and security protocols are clearly defined and aligned with modern retail standards.\n\n## Task Definition\nTo achieve the objective, use the <function>generate_text</function> capability to create a detailed document based on the requirements provided in {{\"type\":\"in\",\"path\":\"LUXE_APP_REQUIREMENTS\",\"title\":\"Luxe App Requirements\"}}. The document must be decomposed into the following specific sections:\n\n1.  **Core Feature Set (Browse Loop):** Detail the user journey for discovery, including the catalog structure, search functionality, and Product Detail Pages (PDP).\n2.  **Transactional Logic (Buy Loop):** Define the logic for cart management, the multi-step checkout process, and secure payment gateway integration.\n3.  **User Management:** Outline the authentication flow (sign-up/login) and user profile management (preferences, order history).\n4.  **Database Logic:** Provide specific table structures for `products`, `cart_items`, and `orders`, including primary/foreign keys and data types.\n5.  **Security & Access Control:** Define Row-Level Security (RLS) rules to ensure data privacy and integrity.\n\n## Definitions and Specifications\nThe generated design must strictly adhere to the following specifications:\n\n*   **Design Aesthetic (Modern Retail):** The UI design philosophy must follow \"Modern Retail\" principles. This means high-contrast typography, ample whitespace, and clean lines. **PROHIBITED:** Do not use gradients or glassmorphism effects.\n*   **Real-Time Capabilities:** The system must support real-time stock updates (e.g., via WebSockets or database subscriptions) to prevent overselling.\n*   **Offline Availability:** The design must include a caching strategy to allow users to view previously loaded products while offline.\n*   **Database Schema Requirements:**\n    *   `products`: Must handle inventory levels, pricing, and metadata.\n    *   `cart_items`: Must link users to products with quantity and state.\n    *   `orders`: Must track transaction status, shipping details, and historical pricing.\n\n## Capabilities Usage\nYou must use the following tool to complete this task:\n*   **<function>generate_text</function>**: Use this tool to synthesize the functional design document. Pass the detailed requirements and the specifications mentioned above into the tool's prompt to ensure all technical and aesthetic constraints are met.\n\n## Requirements for the Ending Response\nThe final response must be a structured functional design document provided in **XML format**. Use the following tag structure:\n\n```xml\n<functional_design_document>\n    <app_overview>...</app_overview>\n    <core_features>\n        <browse_loop>...</browse_loop>\n        <catalog_logic>...</catalog_logic>\n    </core_features>\n    <transactional_logic>\n        <buy_loop>...</buy_loop>\n        <cart_checkout>...</cart_checkout>\n        <payments>...</payments>\n    </transactional_logic>\n    <user_management>\n        <authentication>...</authentication>\n        <profile_logic>...</profile_logic>\n    </user_management>\n    <database_schema>\n        <tables>...</tables>\n    </database_schema>\n    <security_rls>...</security_rls>\n    <technical_specifications>\n        <real_time_updates>...</real_time_updates>\n        <offline_viewing>...</offline_viewing>\n        <design_principles>...</design_principles>\n    </technical_specifications>\n</functional_design_document>\n```\n\n**Constraints:**\n*   **NO** thinking process or \"internal monologue\" should be included in the output.\n*   The response must be **ONLY** the XML document.\n*   Strictly follow the XML schema provided above.\n\n## Execution and Output Reminder\nTake a deep breath and carefully read all instructions and inputs. Think step-by-step about how to solve this task. Use your built-in <function>generate_text</function> capability to gather information and create the required outputs based on {{\"type\":\"in\",\"path\":\"LUXE_APP_REQUIREMENTS\",\"title\":\"Luxe App Requirements\"}}. Ensure your final response meets all format constraints and requirements before outputting it."}],"role":"user"},"generation-mode":"text"}},{"id":"node_step_app_design_document","metadata":{"title":"Render Design Document As Webpage","visual":{"x":1050,"y":350,"collapsed":"expanded","outputHeight":88},"step_intent":"Take the generated functional design document content and render it as a well-formatted HTML webpage. The generate_webpage API will convert the textual content into a presentable HTML output, fulfilling the requirement for the final application output to be an HTML document."},"type":"embed://a2/a2.bgl.json#module:render-outputs","configuration":{"text":{"parts":[{"text":"The webpage should present the functional design document for the LUXE e-commerce app in a professional, modern, and highly readable format. The aesthetic goal is premium, clean, and highly structured, adhering to \"Modern Retail\" principles (no gradients, glassmorphism).\n\n**Layout Organization:**\n\n*   **Overall Structure**:\n    *   A prominent, centered `<header>` at the top of the page containing the main title.\n    *   A `<main>` section encompassing the entire document content.\n    *   A simple `<footer>` at the bottom with copyright information.\n*   **Main Content Layout**:\n    *   The `main` content should be presented within a single, maximum-width container to ensure optimal reading line length, centered on larger screens.\n    *   The content should be divided into distinct `<section>` elements for each major topic (e.g., \"Core Features\", \"Transactional Logic\", \"User Management\", \"Database Logic\", \"Security\").\n    *   Each major section should begin with a clear `<h2>` heading. Sub-sections within these should use `<h3>` headings.\n    *   Text content should be organized into paragraphs (`<p>`), and lists (`<ul>` or `<ol>`) should be used for enumerations or itemized details (e.g., required data fields, checkout steps).\n    *   Database table structures, if detailed, should be presented clearly, potentially using a styled definition list or an actual `<table>` for clarity if the source content naturally lends itself to it.\n*   **Responsive Design**: Implement a mobile-first approach. Content should stack vertically on small screens, with ample padding. On larger screens, content should expand up to a maximum readable width, maintaining generous horizontal margins for an airy feel.\n\n**Style Design Language:**\n\n*   **Visual Design Approach**: Modern, professional, and minimalist with a premium touch. Emphasize clarity, structure, and readability. Avoid ornate decorations, gradients, or heavy shadows to align with \"Modern Retail\" principles.\n*   **Aesthetic Goal**: Premium, professional, clean, and highly readable.\n*   **Color Scheme**:\n    *   **Background**: A soft, off-white or very light grey (#F8F8F8 or similar) to provide a clean canvas.\n    *   **Primary Text**: A sophisticated dark grey or deep charcoal (#333333 or similar) for main body text, ensuring high contrast and readability.\n    *   **Headings/Accent**: A subtle, refined accent color such as a muted deep blue (#005f73), a sophisticated forest green (#2a9d8f), or a deep plum (#6A057F) for headings, links, and potentially subtle separators, indicating professionalism and a touch of \"LUXE\".\n    *   **Subtle Borders/Dividers**: Light grey (#E0E0E0) for any subtle visual separators between sections or elements.\n*   **Typography Style**:\n    *   **Headings (H1, H2, H3)**: A clean, modern sans-serif font with good weight variation (e.g., \"Montserrat\", \"Lato\", \"Inter\"). Use a medium or semi-bold weight for prominence without being too heavy.\n    *   **Body Text**: A highly readable, slightly wider sans-serif font for optimal legibility over long passages (e.g., \"Roboto\", \"Open Sans\", \"Source Sans Pro\"). Use a regular weight.\n    *   **Monospace (for code/technical snippets)**: If any specific database fields or RLS rules are presented in a code-like format, use a clean monospace font (e.g., \"JetBrains Mono\", \"Fira Code\", \"Roboto Mono\").\n*   **Spacing and Layout Principles**:\n    *   **Generous Whitespace**: Utilize ample padding and margins around text blocks and sections to create an open, uncluttered, and premium feel.\n    *   **Clear Vertical Rhythm**: Consistent spacing between paragraphs, list items, and headings to improve readability and visual hierarchy.\n    *   **Line Height**: Ensure comfortable line height (e.g., 1.6-1.8) for body text.\n\n**Component Guidelines:**\n\n*   **Page Title**: `<h1>` for \"LUXE E-Commerce App - Functional Design Document\".\n*   **Section Headings**: `<h2>` for major sections like \"Core Features\", `<h3>` for sub-sections like \"Catalog\", \"Cart\".\n*   **Text Content**: Use `<p>` for paragraphs.\n*   **Lists**: Use `<ul>` for bulleted lists and `<ol>` for ordered lists (e.g., steps in a process).\n*   **Tables (Optional)**: If the database logic includes tabular data, use a clean, borderless `<table>` with distinct `<th>` for headers and `<td>` for data, styled for readability.\n\nluxe_design_content: {{\"type\":\"in\",\"path\":\"node_step_luxe_design_content\",\"title\":\"Generate LUXE Design Content\"}}"}],"role":"user"},"b-system-instruction":{"parts":[{"text":"You are an AI Web Developer. Your task is to generate a single, self-contained HTML document for rendering in an iframe, based on user instructions and data.\n\n**Visual aesthetic:**\n    * Aesthetics are crucial. Make the page look amazing, especially on mobile.\n    * Respect any instructions on style, color palette, or reference examples provided by the user.\n    * **CRITICAL: Aim for premium, state-of-the-art designs. Avoid simple minimum viable products.**\n    * **Use Rich Aesthetics**: The USER should be wowed at first glance by the design. Use best practices in modern web design (e.g. vibrant colors, dark modes, glassmorphism, and dynamic animations) to create a stunning first impression. Failure to do this is UNACCEPTABLE.\n    * **Prioritize Visual Excellence**: Implement designs that will WOW the user and feel extremely premium:\n        - Avoid generic colors (plain red, blue, green). Use curated, harmonious color palettes (e.g., HSL tailored colors, sleek dark modes).\n        - Using modern typography (e.g., from Google Fonts like Inter, Roboto, or Outfit) instead of browser defaults.\n        - Use smooth gradients.\n        - Add subtle micro-animations for enhanced user experience.\n    * **Use a Dynamic Design**: An interface that feels responsive and alive encourages interaction. Achieve this with hover effects and interactive elements. Micro-animations, in particular, are highly effective for improving user engagement.\n    * **Thematic Specificity**: Do not just create a generic layout. Define a clear \"vibe\" or theme based on the content. Use specific aesthetic keywords (e.g., \"Glassmorphism\", \"Neobrutalism\", \"Minimalist\", \"Comic Book Style\") to guide the design.\n    * **Typography Hierarchy**: Explicitly import and use font pairings. Use a distinct Display Font for headers and a highly readable Body Font for text.\n    * **Readability**: Pay extra attention to readability. Ensure the text is always readable with sufficient contrast against the background. Choose fonts and colors that enhance legibility.\n\n**Design and Functionality:**\n    * **Component-Based Design**: Do not just dump text into blocks. Semanticize the content into distinct UI components.\n    * **Layout Dynamics**: Break the grid. Avoid strict, identical grid columns. Use asymmetrical layouts, Bento grids, or responsive flexbox layouts where some elements span full width to create visual interest and emphasize key content.\n    * **Tailwind Configuration**: Extend the Tailwind configuration within a `<script>` block to define custom font families and color palettes that match the theme.\n    * Thoroughly analyze the user's instructions to determine the desired type of webpage, application, or visualization. What are the key features, layouts, or functionality?\n    * Analyze any provided data to identify the most compelling layout or visualization of it. For example, if the user requests a visualization, select an appropriate chart type (bar, line, pie, scatter, etc.) to create the most insightful and visually compelling representation. Or if user instructions say `use a carousel format`, you should consider how to break the content and any media into different card components to display within the carousel.\n    * If requirements are underspecified, make reasonable assumptions to complete the design and functionality. Your goal is to deliver a working product with no placeholder content.\n    * Ensure the generated code is valid and functional. Return only the code, and open the HTML codeblock with the literal string \"```html\".\n    * The output must be a complete and valid HTML document with no placeholder content for the developer to fill in.\n\n**Libraries:**\n  Unless otherwise specified, use:\n    * Tailwind for CSS\n    * **CRITICAL: Use the Tailwind CDN from `https://cdn.tailwindcss.com`. Do NOT use `tailwind.min.css` or any other local Tailwind file. Always include Tailwind using: `<script src=\"https://cdn.tailwindcss.com\"></script>`**\n\n**Constraints:**\n  * **External Links:** You ARE allowed to generate external links (`<a href=\"...\">` and `window.open(...)`) to external websites (e.g. google.com, wikipedia.org) for user navigation.\n  * **NO External Embeds:** Do NOT embed any external resources (e.g. `<script src=\"...\">`, `<img src=\"...\">`, `<iframe src=\"...\">`, `<link href=\"...\">`) from external URLs. Content Security Policy (CSP) will block them.\n  * **Media Restriction:** ONLY use media URLs that are explicitly passed in the input. Do NOT generate or hallucinate any other media URLs (e.g. from placeholder sites or external CDNs).\n  * **Render All Media:** You MUST render ALL media (images, videos, audio) that are passed in. Do NOT skip or omit any provided media items. Every passed-in media URL must appear in the final HTML output.\n  * **Navigation Restriction:** Do NOT generate unneeded fake links or buttons to sub-pages (e.g. \"About\", \"Contact\", \"Learn More\") unless explicitly requested. Stick to the plan and the provided content.\n  * **Footer Restriction:** **NEVER** generate any footer content, including legal footers like \"All rights reserved\" or \"Copyright 2024\". [It is a violation of Google's policies to hallucinate legal footers.]\n"}],"role":"user"},"p-render-mode":"Auto","b-render-model-name":"gemini-flash"}},{"id":"4c4e49f9-01ec-4dc3-9e83-13d7652c23a6","type":"embed://a2/a2.bgl.json#module:render-outputs","metadata":{"title":"Output","visual":{"x":900,"y":340},"userModified":false},"configuration":{"p-render-mode":"google-doc","text":{"role":"user","parts":[{"text":""}]}}}],"edges":[{"from":"node_step_luxe_design_content","to":"node_step_app_design_document","out":"context","in":"p-z-node_step_luxe_design_content"}],"url":"drive:/16XGeC2sHNs0jNSdjPS4mnD8bKsAdGx1J"}